\f1\fs22 2.3 Mix & Reverb Controls\f0\fs22\par
\par
\i [Insert screenshot: Centre panel with Dry/Wet, Predelay, Damping, Stretch, Width, etc.]\i0\par
\par
\b Dry / Wet\b0  (0-100%) - Balance between dry (original) and wet (reverb) signal.\par
\b Predelay\b0  (0-500 ms) - Delay before the reverb starts.\par
\b Damping\b0  (0-100%) - High-frequency damping. Higher = more dull decay.\par
\b Stretch\b0  (0.5-2.0) - Time-stretches the IR. 1.0 = no change.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 2.4 Stereo & Modulation\f0\fs22\par
\par
\b Width\b0  (0-2) - Stereo width of the wet signal. 1 = normal, less than 1 = narrower, greater than 1 = wider.\par
\b LFO Depth\b0  (0-1) - Depth of LFO modulation applied to the tail.\par
\b LFO Rate\b0  (0.01-2 Hz) - Speed of the LFO modulation.\par
\b Tail Mod\b0  (0-1) - Amount of modulation on the reverb tail.\par
\b Delay Depth\b0  (0.5-8 ms) - Modulated delay depth.\par
\b Rate\b0  (0.05-3 Hz) - Rate of tail modulation.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 2.5 IR Input\f0\fs22\par
\par
\b IR Input Gain\b0  (-24 to +12 dB) - Gain applied to the signal before convolution.\par
\b IR Input Drive\b0  (0-1) - Saturation/drive before convolution. Higher values add warmth.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 2.6 Early Reflections & Tail Balance\f0\fs22\par
\par
\b ER (Early Reflections)\b0  (-48 to +6 dB) - Level of the early reflection portion of the IR.\par
\b Tail\b0  (-48 to +6 dB) - Level of the late reverb tail.\par
\par
Use these to rebalance IRs that have strong early or late content.\par
\par

