\f1\fs24 4. Technical Explanation: How the IR is Synthesised\f0\fs22\par
\par
P!NG uses a geometric acoustic engine to produce a true-stereo, 4-channel IR (LL, RL, LR, RR) for convolution reverb.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.1 Overview\f0\fs22\par
\par
1. Image-source method - Mirror sources for early reflections.\par
2. Per-band rendering - Six octave bands for frequency-dependent absorption.\par
3. Allpass diffusion - Smoothes reflections.\par
4. FDN tail - 16-delay feedback delay network for late reverb.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.2 Image-Source Method\f0\fs22\par
\par
Virtual sources mirror the real source across floor, ceiling, and walls. Each reflection has delay (path length / speed of sound) and per-band amplitudes from distance attenuation, floor/ceiling/wall absorption, air absorption, mic polar pattern, speaker directivity (cardioid), and polarity (flipped on odd bounces).\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.3 Per-Band Rendering\f0\fs22\par
\par
Materials have absorption coefficients at 125-4000 Hz. The engine splits reflections into six bands, applies band-specific absorption, bandpass-filters each band, and sums into a single time series per channel. Produces frequency-dependent decay.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.4 Diffusion\f0\fs22\par
\par
A 4-stage allpass diffusion network smooths the summed signal. Higher diffusion increases delay density and reduces flutter.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.5 Late Reverb (FDN Tail)\f0\fs22\par
\par
After ~85 ms: Early part from image-source feeds a 16-line FDN. Delays are prime-numbered, scaled by mean free path. LFO modulation reduces metallic resonances. Hadamard mixing distributes energy. Per-line lowpass gives frequency-dependent decay. Early and tail crossfaded at 85 ms.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.6 Output\f0\fs22\par
\par
4-channel IR: iLL, iRL, iLR, iRR. Band-limited 20 Hz-18 kHz, normalised, 24-bit WAV. .ping sidecar stores synthesis parameters.\par
\par

\f1\fs22 4.7 RT60 Calculation\f0\fs22\par
\par
Eyring equation: T = 0.161 x V / (-S x ln(1 - a)) where V = volume, S = surface area, a = average absorption. Air absorption, audience, balconies, organ included.\par
\par
